oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Garrett Family Home
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Malcolm Garrett's house located on the east side of the processing plant in Old Town section of Celina. Mrs. Garrett is pointing to a hole in the wall made by a cannonball during the Battle of Celina in 1863.
The house burned down in the 1970's.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:source: Looking Back at Tennessee Photograph Collection, 1890-1981
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:subject: Houses; Dwellings; Holes; War damage
